FBIS3-32772 "drlat030_r_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 Peru Government Silent on Resignation Reports PA1202032794 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 0100 GMT 12 Feb 94 PA1202032794 Lima Global de Television Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "Global TV News" newscast] [Text] The government palace has maintained total silence since the promulgation of the law on venue dispute and amid rumors of the resignations of two ministers. President Alberto Fujimori has continued to work privately without making any public appearances for the past three days. The government palace press secretariat also declined to provide information on the rumored resignations of Council of Ministers President Alfonso Bustamante y Bustamante, who did not sign the law, and Economy Minister Jorge Camet.
